 Port Elizabeth - The police in New Brighton are searching for 26-year-old Andile Dingani, who was reported missing by his father on 24 May 2020. "He was last seen leaving his home in Ferguson Road, New Brighton at about 00:00 on 15 May 2020 for unknown reasons and never returned," said police spokesperson, Captain Andre Beetge. "He was wearing black jeans, green t-shirt, black jacket and white Adidas tekkies and is 1, 74 metre tall. "Any person that could assist the police in finding Andile can contact the investigating officer, Detective Sergeant Alexander Pio at 076 332 2249." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 